{
  "stem": "11723.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 100,
      "text": "Except that during her time in the ghetto, she gave birth to-- I don't know if it was a boy or girl-- and she had no milk to give the child, and the child died.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 101,
      "text": "And my aunt carried the dead child around for I don't know how long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 102,
      "text": "And she-- she went insane.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 103,
      "text": "And her insanity manifested itself, among other things, by not eating anything-- starving even when food was available.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 104,
      "text": "And my [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] other uncle, my father's older brother who had a child and a wife with my grandmothers who died in Varosmajor, along with the grandmothers.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 105,
      "text": "He never recovered from that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 106,
      "text": "He-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he finally came to this country and he's-- he has a degree in chemical engineering.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 107,
      "text": "And he ended up being a busboy even though he spoke English, because he just lost all interest in life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- but he did totally insane things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like he-- he found some-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you know what Napoleons are?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Those gold coins.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He found a hundred Napoleons some place that Grandma put away somewhere.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was getting ready to leave the country in 1946, and [LAUGHS] he-- he was going to take it with him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he went and he melted it down into blocks-- I mean rods.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When my father found that, he flipped.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He couldn't believe that his brother had gone totally crazy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, my mother's oldest brother didn't come back from slave labor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His wife and his five children were burnt in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at that time in 1945, getting food in Hungary-- at least in the city-- was extremely difficult.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was starvation practically.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in order to nurse us back to health, my mother needed to have plenty of food for us.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
